	<p>The dog breeder is a job for dedicated people. In order to decide to become them, you need to give up a lot. <br> Question - in the name of what? In the name of victories at exhibitions? In the name of charming puppies? In the name of numerous dogs, who take away the last time and energy, but because of their favorite every day more and more ... <br> I think that if you give up something in the name of someone, it is only for good luck, caught by the tail. Even if it is the tail of a Labrador. Among the breeders, outright "lucky ones" are a rarity. From the very beginning, their career develops successfully in all respects. Whether due to a subtle intuition, a balanced and reasonable approach or simple luck. Be that as it may, they have become successful, they are equal to them, they envy them. For a long time, I will, willy-nilly, observe the nursery of labradors "Timantti Solid." It is impossible to say that this breed was close to me, since in the presence of my own Golden, in my heart I am a “terrier”. But something always attracted me in this cattery. I think the extraordinary personality of his owner Tatyana Dreyer is a breeder not only with his name, experience and experience, but also an FCI expert, and one of the best, in my understanding. I like balanced and sensible breeders who do not climb on the rampage, do not tear the shirt on his chest, trying to prove something to someone, but calmly and purposefully, like powerful dreadnoughts, go to their goal and achieve it calmly and without too much pathos. And failures such breeders perceive without hysteria and tragedy, with philosophical calm. So maybe it is from such breeders to learn something? Perhaps their luck magically teleports to others and the world of dog breeding replenished with new "lucky"?...</p>
